RADIO presenter Moeti “Mo Flava” Tsiki left many of his followers chuckling when he decided to wear a dress. The 38-year-old from Dube, Soweto, was doing a birthday challenge with co-presenters Lindi Sirame and Khutso Theledi on their breakfast show, Wake Up With Mo Flava on Metro FM. He took to Instagram on Wednesday, 20 J0uly, to post photos of himself in a dress, adding that the challenge made him feel weird. He wrote: “And so I was challenged to dress as @lindi_serame and @KhutsoTheledi. My team is so loving.” ALSO READ : Ayeye back on screens! Mo Flava said this was the most challenging out-of-body experience as he was not used to wearing dresses. “Quite an out-of-body experience I must say. This birthday challenge must fall, seriously,” he said. Most of his followers took to the comment section with laughter. Dr Sivuyile Madikana said Mo Flava had a beautiful waist. “Yas moghel. All hail, queen,” said Chymamusique. Then I am PH wrote: “Hawu, aus Mo. Nguwe Lo?” Zola Hashatsi added that he thought he was seeing Mo Flava’s twin sister. A post shared by Moflava (@moflava)  